data.name: label7.Text
data.value: As for calorie burning, the rate varies depending on factors such as swimming stroke, intensity, duration, and individual factors like weight and fitness level. On average, swimming can burn approximately 400-600 calories per hour for a person weighing around 150 pounds. However, the calorie expenditure can be higher for more vigorous strokes or longer swim sessions.

data.name: lblSwimDescription.Text
data.value: Swimming is a form of physical activity and exercise that involves propelling oneself through water using various swimming strokes. It can be done for recreation, sport, fitness, or as a competitive activity.
